Water and Sanitation Minister, Lindiwe Sisulu says if the country uses water sparingly, there will be no need for water-shedding. Sisulu, however, said water restrictions will have to be implemented. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Water and Sanitation Minister Lindiwe Sisulu says if the country uses water sparingly, there will be no need for water-shedding. Sisulu, however, said water restrictions will have to be implemented. WATCH: Joburg taps running low She was briefing the media on the status of the country's dam levels. Sisulu said high temperatures also impacted the water situation.